phrase, one part of the phrase

00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:51.420
has this accentuation, or this
effect, that the rest of it

00:13:51.420 --> 00:13:52.110
doesn't have.

00:13:52.110 --> 00:13:56.310
And that can be a
tremendous, dramatic change.

00:13:56.310 --> 00:13:59.060
But to keep it short,
there's a delay.

00:13:59.060 --> 00:14:04.960
There is kind of like
a pitch bend idea.

00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:07.590
There is a flute player
you guys might have heard,

00:14:07.590 --> 00:14:11.230
a gun named Robert Dick,
who made a glissando

00:14:11.230 --> 00:14:13.250
head for the flute.

00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:19.250
And the way it works is,
it slides in and out.

00:14:19.250 --> 00:14:24.700
So you play a note, and
there's a thumb thing.

00:14:24.700 --> 00:14:29.180
And use this thumb thing,
lever, whatever it is,

00:14:29.180 --> 00:14:31.210
to make this head joint slide.

00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:33.149
So I think that the blow
hole's not changing,

00:14:33.149 --> 00:14:35.315
but I think something on
this side of the head joint

00:14:35.315 --> 00:14:35.815
is changing.

00:14:35.815 --> 00:14:37.856
So the glissando flute.

