00:16:16.180 --> 00:16:19.830
It's using anybody's intel,
like audio engineering.

00:16:19.830 --> 00:16:22.860
It's using fast Fourier
transforms, which basically

00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:26.430
take a snapshot of
the sound, in terms

00:16:26.430 --> 00:16:31.630
of the pitches that
are in the sound.

00:16:31.630 --> 00:16:35.540
Remember when we looked at that
piece of software last week?

00:16:35.540 --> 00:16:37.200
We took, I think
a trombone sample,

00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:38.430
