00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:47.600
So for software like that, you
can take a so-called frame,

00:16:47.600 --> 00:16:49.960
we'll say it's a
24th of a second,

00:16:49.960 --> 00:16:54.730
and do a spectral analysis
of that 24th of a second.

00:16:54.730 --> 00:16:56.010
And then freeze it.

00:16:56.010 --> 00:17:09.569
Just play those frequencies
in the frequency domain,

00:17:09.569 --> 00:17:10.410
and just hold it.

00:17:10.410 --> 00:17:14.079
